This paper deals with information-theoretic security and authentication schemes, which are typically studied in the computer security (cs.CR) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. The use of hash functions and the universal composability framework also suggest the computer cryptography (cs.CC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the trace distance, which is a concept used in quantum information theory, suggesting the computer engineering (cs.CE) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
